1834:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *
1835:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     * \brief
1836:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  Executes the IDAC calibration for all the sensors in the widget specified in
1837:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  the input.
1838:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *
1839:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     * \details
1840:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  Performs a successive approximation search algorithm to find appropriate
1841:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  IDAC values for sensors in the specified widget that provides the raw
1842:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  count to the level specified by the target parameter.
1843:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *
1844:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  Calibration is always performed in the single IDAC mode and if the dual
1845:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  IDAC mode (Enable compensation IDAC is enabled) is configured, the IDAC
1846:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  values are re-calculated to match the raw count target. If a widget
1847:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  consists of two or more elements (buttons, slider segments, etc.), then
1848:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  calibration is performed by the element with the highest sensor
1849:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  capacitance.
1850:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *
1851:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  Calibration fails if the achieved raw count is outside of the +/-10%
1852:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  range of the target.
1853:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *
1854:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  This function is available when the CSD Enable IDAC auto-calibration
1855:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  parameter is enabled or the  SmartSense auto-tuning mode is configured.
1856:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *
1857:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     * \param widgetId
1858:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  Specifies the ID number of the CSD widget to calibrate its raw count.
1859:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  A macro for the widget ID can be found in the
1860:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  CapSense Configuration header file defined as
1861:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  CapSense_<WidgetName>_WDGT_ID.
1862:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *
1863:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     * \param target
1864:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  Specifies the calibration target in percentages of the maximum raw count.
1865:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *
1866:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     * \return
1867:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *  Returns the status of the specified widget calibration:
1868:Generated_Source\PSoC6/CapSense_SensingCSD_LL.c ****     *    - CY_RET_SUCCESS - The operation is successfully completed.
